data.content:
past participle of 1know
adjective
always used before a noun
generally accepted as something specified
He's a known expert.
That's a known fact!
a known criminal
included in the knowledge that all people considered as one group have
There is no known cure for the disease. [=there is no cure that anyone knows about, although a cure may exist that has not yet been discovered]
the earliest known use of a word [=the earliest use that anyone knows about]
familiar to people - used with little, widely, etc.
a widely known story [=a story that many people know]
a little-known writer [=a writer that few people know about] - see also well-known
known quantity
xem quantity
